First modify the variables in tools/variables.sh and vars.mk. Do a 
"make && make install" to install the kernel and boot modules. to
the disk. 

A disk image can be associated with a loopback device, for
example, by doing a "losetup /dev/loop2 os_disk.img" (os_disk.img 
is associated with /dev/loop2). The loopback device can then be used
like a physical device. 
